1. Kafka — REAL SYSTEM THINKING (Not Just Tool)
🔥 What Kafka REALLY is

👉 Apache Kafka is NOT just a queue.

👉 It is:

Distributed commit log (append-only, immutable event store)

🧠 Key Insight (INTERVIEW GOLD)

👉 Kafka stores history of events, not just messages.

Event 1 → Event 2 → Event 3 → Event 4

👉 Consumers can:

Read from beginning
Replay events
Recover state
🎯 Interview Answer
❓ “What is Kafka?”

✅ Distributed, fault-tolerant event streaming platform with persistent logs

🟢 2. Kafka Core Concepts (DEEP UNDERSTANDING)
🔹 1. Topic

👉 Logical stream of data
Example:

orders-topic
transactions-topic
🔹 2. Partition (CRITICAL)

👉 Topic is split into partitions:

orders-topic
   ├── partition-0
   ├── partition-1
   ├── partition-2
🧠 Why partitions?
Parallel processing
Scalability
Ordering guarantee (within partition)
🎯 Interview Answer
❓ “Is Kafka ordered?”

✅ Yes — only within a partition

🔹 3. Offset

👉 Each message has unique position:

offset: 0, 1, 2, 3...
🧠 Why offset matters?
Tracks progress
Enables retries
Prevents data loss
🔹 4. Producer

👉 Sends events to Kafka

🔹 5. Consumer

👉 Reads events

🔹 6. Consumer Group (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Multiple consumers share load

🧠 Example:
orders-topic → 3 partitions
consumer-group → 3 consumers

👉 Each consumer handles one partition

