🟡 4. Python Kafka — PRODUCTION THINKING
🔹 Producer (Better Version)
from kafka import KafkaProducer
import json

producer = KafkaProducer(
    bootstrap_servers='localhost:9092',
    acks='all',  # reliability
    retries=3,
    value_serializer=lambda v: json.dumps(v).encode('utf-8')
)

def send_event(event):
    producer.send("orders-topic", event)
    producer.flush()
🧠 Important configs
Config	Purpose
acks='all'	durability
retries	fault tolerance
🔹 Consumer (Better Version)
from kafka import KafkaConsumer
import json

consumer = KafkaConsumer(
    'orders-topic',
    bootstrap_servers='localhost:9092',
    group_id='portfolio-group',
    auto_offset_reset='earliest',
    enable_auto_commit=False,
    value_deserializer=lambda x: json.loads(x.decode('utf-8'))
)

for msg in consumer:
    event = msg.value
    print("Processing:", event)

    # Process event
    consumer.commit()
🧠 Key Insight

👉 Manual commit = better control + reliability

